  "publisher": "anime",
  "about": "Jujutsu Kaisen (呪術廻戦; rgh. 'Sorcery Battle') is a Japanese anime television series produced by MAPPA, based on the manga series Jujutsu Kaisen by Gege Akutami. The story focuses on high school student Yuji Itadori as he joins a secret organization of Jujutsu Sorcerers to eliminate a powerful Curse named Ryomen Sukuna, of whom Yuji becomes the host. The series broadcasts on MBS, TBS and their JNN affiliates in Japan. Crunchyroll licensed the series for worldwide streaming outside of Asia and launched an English dub in November 2020. The anime's original soundtrack was released in April 2021.\nA film set before the events of the main series, Jujutsu Kaisen 0, was released in Japan by Toho in December 2021. It adapts the prequel manga series Jujutsu Kaisen 0, also by Gege Akutami.",
